<div class=3D"report-wrap">

  <div class=3D"report-header">
    <div class=3D"report-eyebrow">Market Intelligence Report</div>
    <h1 class=3D"report-title">Demand Monitoring &amp; Market Timing:<br><e=
m>GPUs, Consoles, &amp; Collectibles</em></h1>
    <div class=3D"report-meta">
      <div class=3D"report-meta-item"><strong>Period:</strong> January to J=
une 2023</div>
      <div class=3D"report-meta-item"><strong>Analyst:</strong> Emily Moeun=
g</div>
      <div class=3D"report-meta-item"><strong>Context:</strong> Market Stra=
tegy Intern, Majestix</div>
      <div class=3D"report-meta-item"><strong>Indicators:</strong> CPI, Sti=
mulus Flows, Crypto Demand, Supply Chain Data</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class=3D"exec-summary">
    <div class=3D"exec-label">Executive Summary</div>
    <p class=3D"exec-text">
      Working in the secondary market space, the core task was always the s=
ame: identify what people want, source it before the broader market catches=
 on, and move it at the right time. Doing that consistently required unders=
tanding <em>why</em> prices move, not just tracking them. This report synth=
esizes the economic research and market analysis that informed those sourci=
ng decisions across GPUs, Consoles, &amp; Collectibles. The 2020=E2=80=9320=
22 period created some of the most volatile secondary market conditions in =
recent history =E2=80=94 driven by <strong>government stimulus, a crypto mi=
ning boom, and global chip shortages</strong> =E2=80=94 and understanding t=
hat backdrop was essential to making sense of where prices stood in 2023 an=
d where they were heading.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 1: MACRO -->
  <div class=3D"section">
    <div class=3D"section-num">01 =E2=80=94 Macroeconomic Context</div>
    <div class=3D"section-title">How Stimulus Money Turbocharged Consumer E=
lectronics Demand</div>
    <p class=3D"section-body">
      Between March 2020 and March 2021, the U.S. government issued three r=
ounds of direct stimulus payments totaling up to <strong>$3,200 per eligibl=
e adult</strong>, alongside the Paycheck Protection Program (PPP) which inj=
ected over $800 billion into the economy. With lockdowns in place, physical=
 spending curtailed, and remote work driving the need for upgraded home set=
ups, a significant portion of this liquidity flowed directly into consumer =
electronics. Simultaneously, cryptocurrency prices surged, with Bitcoin rea=
ching <strong>$69,000 in November 2021</strong> and Ethereum peaking above =
$4,800. Because Ethereum used an ASIC-resistant mining algorithm, GPUs rema=
ined the only viable mining hardware, creating a second massive demand chan=
nel for graphics cards that distribution networks were never designed to ha=
ndle. At the height of the boom, crypto miners accounted for an estimated <=
strong>25% of all GPU purchases</strong> in the first half of 2021, accordi=
ng to Jon Peddie Research.
    </p>

    <div class=3D"insights">
      <div class=3D"insight">
        <div class=3D"insight-n" style=3D"color:var(--blue);">$3,200</div>
        <div class=3D"insight-label">Stimulus Per Adult</div>
        <div class=3D"insight-desc">Three rounds of direct payments (Mar 20=
20, Dec 2020, Mar 2021) injected unprecedented discretionary spending into =
electronics and collectibles markets.</div>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"insight">
        <div class=3D"insight-n" style=3D"color:var(--orange);">$69K</div>
        <div class=3D"insight-label">BTC Peak (Nov 2021)</div>
        <div class=3D"insight-desc">Bitcoin's price spike made GPU mining h=
ighly profitable, adding a second massive demand driver on top of the gamin=
g and remote work surge.</div>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"insight">
        <div class=3D"insight-n" style=3D"color:var(--green);">9.1%</div>
        <div class=3D"insight-label">Peak Inflation (Jun 2022)</div>
        <div class=3D"insight-desc">As liquidity flooded the economy, infla=
tion peaked, shrinking consumer spending by 2023 and triggering a secondary=
 market correction.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"chart-card">
      <div class=3D"chart-title">U.S. CPI Inflation Rate vs. Bitcoin Price,=
 2021=E2=80=932023</div>
      <div class=3D"chart-wrap"><canvas id=3D"macroChart" width=3D"1524" he=
ight=3D"480" style=3D"display: block; box-sizing: border-box; height: 240px=
; width: 762px;"></canvas></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 2: METHODOLOGY -->
  <div class=3D"section">
    <div class=3D"section-num">02 =E2=80=94 Monitoring Methodology</div>
    <div class=3D"section-title">How Demand Signals Were Tracked in Real Ti=
me</div>
    <p class=3D"section-body">
      The research approach combined <strong>macroeconomic analysis with fi=
eld-level observation</strong>, using economic indicators to establish the =
broader demand context, then validating those signals through direct vendor=
 engagement and consumer behavior observed at live events. This dual-layer =
methodology allowed for higher-confidence sourcing decisions, as quantitati=
ve models were tested against real-world conditions rather than applied in =
isolation.
    </p>

